1
00:03:25,600 --> 00:03:27,000
CHOKUDOMSAP 8

2
00:06:57,240 --> 00:07:03,840
YEARS LATER

3
00:07:32,320 --> 00:07:34,440
Are you sure you didn't forget anything?

4
00:07:40,280 --> 00:07:41,280
Probably not.

5
00:07:42,400 --> 00:07:44,480
But even if I did, what's the big deal?

6
00:07:44,560 --> 00:07:46,080
I can just come back and get it.

7
00:07:47,640 --> 00:07:49,000
I'm more worried you won't come back.

8
00:07:50,960 --> 00:07:53,960
The place we're going isn't just
five or ten minutes away, you know.

9
00:07:54,040 --> 00:07:56,360
It's about two hours from shore.

10
00:07:57,000 --> 00:07:58,000
I know.

11
00:07:58,080 --> 00:08:00,280
But what you still haven't told me is…

12
00:08:02,920 --> 00:08:04,560
from this main island

13
00:08:04,640 --> 00:08:06,280
to the diving spot,

14
00:08:07,640 --> 00:08:09,080
how long does it take?

15
00:08:09,760 --> 00:08:10,600
An hour.

16
00:08:12,360 --> 00:08:15,000
Hey. Tell me.

17
00:08:15,080 --> 00:08:17,320
Is there some rare fish
you wanna photograph there?

18
00:08:18,680 --> 00:08:19,640
Something like that.

19
00:08:20,240 --> 00:08:23,680
You going there to preserve fish
or looking for something else?

20
00:08:25,200 --> 00:08:27,160
Is there something to look for?

21
00:08:29,960 --> 00:08:32,919
Pong, the boat's ready.

22
00:08:33,600 --> 00:08:34,600
The boat's ready.

23
00:08:35,440 --> 00:08:37,720
What about you? You ready yet?

24
00:08:40,679 --> 00:08:41,679
I'm ready.

25
00:08:46,640 --> 00:08:49,160
The thing you need
to be most careful about

26
00:08:49,240 --> 00:08:51,840
when you rise to the surface

27
00:08:51,920 --> 00:08:54,280
is that the air you breathe from the tank

28
00:08:54,360 --> 00:08:56,000
will expand.

29
00:08:56,080 --> 00:08:57,920
If you hold your breath,

30
00:08:58,000 --> 00:09:00,320
your lungs could rupture.

31
00:09:01,440 --> 00:09:02,400
I know that.

32
00:09:04,000 --> 00:09:05,160
Good.

33
00:09:05,920 --> 00:09:07,320
But a ruptured lung

34
00:09:07,400 --> 00:09:09,640
and losing your nerve
are two different things.

35
00:09:11,080 --> 00:09:12,400
- Let's go.
- Nice, bro.

36
00:09:28,520 --> 00:09:31,400
Look ahead. Don't turn around.

37
00:09:31,480 --> 00:09:33,280
The moment you look back, you die!

38
00:09:36,440 --> 00:09:37,440
What's wrong with him?

39
00:09:39,320 --> 00:09:41,560
He's just a madman. Don't mind him.

40
00:09:41,640 --> 00:09:42,760
Just leave him alone.

41
00:09:56,560 --> 00:09:58,040
Don't go. Don't go!

42
00:09:58,120 --> 00:09:59,920
Don't. Don't go!

43
00:10:01,400 --> 00:10:02,440
What are you talking about?

44
00:10:03,720 --> 00:10:06,880
Look ahead. Don't turn around.

45
00:10:06,960 --> 00:10:09,240
The moment you look back, you die!

46
00:10:09,840 --> 00:10:12,280
- Die!
- Hey, sir? What are you talking about?

47
00:10:12,360 --> 00:10:13,640
‪Die…

48
00:10:14,200 --> 00:10:17,160
It's in the water.

49
00:10:17,240 --> 00:10:19,480
It's dark. It's scary.

50
00:10:20,080 --> 00:10:21,880
Die! Die!

51
00:10:21,960 --> 00:10:23,800
- Die!
- Sir.

52
00:10:24,400 --> 00:10:26,080
Hey.

53
00:10:26,160 --> 00:10:28,960
Go away if you don't wanna get hurt.

54
00:10:29,040 --> 00:10:31,280
It's dark.

55
00:10:31,360 --> 00:10:32,960
Dark my ass. Get lost!

56
00:10:33,040 --> 00:10:33,880
Madman.

57
00:10:33,960 --> 00:10:36,560
- It's so bright.
- Go away.

58
00:10:37,560 --> 00:10:40,080
- We're working now.
- Hey.

59
00:10:40,640 --> 00:10:41,920
I told you to leave him alone.

60
00:10:43,160 --> 00:10:44,120
Let's go.

61
00:14:33,400 --> 00:14:34,960
I really saw it.

62
00:14:36,440 --> 00:14:38,880
It wasn't a rock,

63
00:14:38,960 --> 00:14:40,400
but I'm not sure it was coral either.

64
00:14:41,400 --> 00:14:42,440
Coral?

65
00:14:44,880 --> 00:14:46,320
I don't know.

66
00:14:49,520 --> 00:14:51,560
Where's the picture?

67
00:14:53,240 --> 00:14:56,480
The water was so murky.
Maybe you imagined it.

68
00:14:57,040 --> 00:14:58,640
Maybe.

69
00:15:00,560 --> 00:15:03,040
I should've swum a little closer.

70
00:15:04,440 --> 00:15:07,040
Good thing you didn't.

71
00:15:07,120 --> 00:15:10,720
With currents that strong, you could've
been sucked in and never made it back out.

72
00:15:12,960 --> 00:15:15,280
Are the currents normally like that?

73
00:15:16,640 --> 00:15:19,640
Depends on the season and the weather.

74
00:15:22,600 --> 00:15:25,440
But the weather was fine when we went out.

75
00:15:35,440 --> 00:15:38,400
None of the underwater photos came out.

76
00:15:38,480 --> 00:15:41,440
But the photos
I took on land and on the boat

77
00:15:41,520 --> 00:15:42,880
are all there.

78
00:15:50,200 --> 00:15:51,800
Maybe that's a good thing.

79
00:15:52,520 --> 00:15:54,480
Better than capturing something scary.

80
00:15:57,320 --> 00:15:58,880
Maybe the camera's busted.

81
00:16:26,680 --> 00:16:30,080
Look ahead. Don't turn around.

82
00:16:35,320 --> 00:16:36,560
If you turn back,

83
00:16:37,360 --> 00:16:38,720
you die.

84
00:17:15,800 --> 00:17:17,599
For underwater photography,

85
00:17:17,680 --> 00:17:19,800
I never use zoom

86
00:17:19,880 --> 00:17:22,599
because it increases the distance
between the camera and the subject.

87
00:17:22,680 --> 00:17:26,520
That reduces both sharpness
and color quality.

88
00:17:27,800 --> 00:17:31,640
So that means
you get really close to the subject?

89
00:17:32,400 --> 00:17:33,360
Yes.

90
00:17:33,440 --> 00:17:36,320
And when you think you're close enough,
you actually need to get even closer.

91
00:17:37,400 --> 00:17:39,240
What about shutter speed?

92
00:17:39,840 --> 00:17:41,120
It depends.

93
00:17:41,200 --> 00:17:43,320
For stationary subjects

94
00:17:43,400 --> 00:17:46,040
like starfish, coral,

95
00:17:46,120 --> 00:17:47,480
or rocks,

96
00:17:47,560 --> 00:17:49,200
it should be set at the lowest.

97
00:17:49,280 --> 00:17:52,200
It shouldn't go
beyond one-30th of a second.

98
00:17:53,920 --> 00:17:55,240
I have a question.

99
00:17:56,640 --> 00:18:00,640
And what if you need to photograph
mysterious underwater entities?

100
00:18:02,200 --> 00:18:05,000
Mysterious entities? Like what?

101
00:18:05,680 --> 00:18:07,240
Well,

102
00:18:07,320 --> 00:18:10,120
ghosts, demons, underwater spirits.

103
00:18:12,560 --> 00:18:14,800
There's no need
to adjust the shutter at all.

104
00:18:14,880 --> 00:18:16,680
Because no matter how you shoot,
you won't capture them.

105
00:18:18,280 --> 00:18:21,640
But if they want to show up,
they'll show up on their own.

106
00:18:24,440 --> 00:18:27,240
I have no further questions. Do any of
the other professors have any questions?

107
00:18:27,320 --> 00:18:28,400
No for me.

108
00:18:28,480 --> 00:18:30,200
Me neither.

109
00:18:30,920 --> 00:18:34,440
Alright.
That was all of my presentation today.

110
00:18:34,520 --> 00:18:35,480
Thank you.

111
00:18:37,000 --> 00:18:38,400
Good job.

112
00:19:01,760 --> 00:19:03,560
RESERVED BY MR. PHUM WITASSANAI

113
00:19:08,800 --> 00:19:09,680
RESERVED BY MR. PHUM

114
00:19:12,200 --> 00:19:13,920
RESERVED BY MR. PHUM

115
00:19:14,000 --> 00:19:15,840
RESERVED BY MR. PHUM WITASSANAI

116
00:19:15,920 --> 00:19:17,280
RESERVED BY MR. PHUM WITASSANAI

117
00:19:17,360 --> 00:19:18,600
RESERVED BY MR. PHUM WITASSANAI

118
00:19:37,160 --> 00:19:38,320
Black coral.

119
00:19:40,080 --> 00:19:42,560
The angel of the sea.

120
00:19:47,680 --> 00:19:49,800
The angel of the sea?

121
00:19:49,880 --> 00:19:52,760
Yes. What do you think?

122
00:19:56,840 --> 00:19:57,760
It's amazing.

123
00:19:58,480 --> 00:20:00,040
Black coral.

124
00:20:02,640 --> 00:20:03,920
It's a type of coral called

125
00:20:04,000 --> 00:20:05,800
"Antipatharia."

126
00:20:07,080 --> 00:20:08,160
Right.

127
00:20:08,240 --> 00:20:10,200
But this isn't one.

128
00:20:13,680 --> 00:20:14,880
I don't understand.

129
00:20:16,960 --> 00:20:20,240
It's actually a photo of a large coral

130
00:20:20,320 --> 00:20:23,040
taken against the light shining down
from the surface.

131
00:20:23,760 --> 00:20:26,240
That's why it looks like black coral.

132
00:20:26,320 --> 00:20:28,280
It isn't actually Antipatharia.

133
00:20:30,240 --> 00:20:31,320
Really?

134
00:20:35,960 --> 00:20:38,040
How do you know?

135
00:20:39,680 --> 00:20:41,800
Because I took the photo.

136
00:20:43,280 --> 00:20:45,480
- Kaimook?
- Yes.

137
00:20:45,560 --> 00:20:47,600
You're Kaimook?

138
00:20:47,680 --> 00:20:49,400
Yes, that's me.

139
00:20:50,000 --> 00:20:51,520
Oh.

140
00:20:51,600 --> 00:20:53,240
You like this photo, don't you?

141
00:20:53,320 --> 00:20:54,520
No, I don't.

142
00:20:55,040 --> 00:20:56,160
Oh?

143
00:20:57,160 --> 00:20:58,480
Is it not beautiful?

144
00:20:59,320 --> 00:21:01,560
No. It's not beautiful. It's terrible.

145
00:21:24,400 --> 00:21:25,320
Hey, my friend.

146
00:21:27,200 --> 00:21:28,160
Yeah, hi.

147
00:21:29,640 --> 00:21:30,760
You're so early.

148
00:21:30,840 --> 00:21:32,760
Sorry, man.

149
00:21:32,840 --> 00:21:35,480
I had to sign some documents,
so I came down late.

150
00:21:36,880 --> 00:21:39,840
You already saw the exhibition, right?
How was it?

151
00:21:40,880 --> 00:21:43,200
It was good. Beautiful.

152
00:21:44,520 --> 00:21:45,520
Not bad.

153
00:21:45,600 --> 00:21:47,960
What's wrong with you?
Just say if you like it or not?

154
00:21:48,040 --> 00:21:49,440
I don't.

155
00:21:52,440 --> 00:21:53,760
Give me a reason.

156
00:21:55,160 --> 00:21:56,240
No reason.

157
00:21:58,000 --> 00:21:59,920
And I don't understand.

158
00:22:00,000 --> 00:22:01,360
What don't you understand?

159
00:22:02,560 --> 00:22:04,680
I don't understand who that girl is.

160
00:22:05,400 --> 00:22:08,800
And why did my father
reserve every single piece here?

161
00:22:09,400 --> 00:22:10,400
Satisfied?

162
00:22:11,680 --> 00:22:14,400
No. Just tell me straight.

163
00:22:14,480 --> 00:22:16,440
Why did you come here?

164
00:22:22,160 --> 00:22:23,920
If it's this model,

165
00:22:24,600 --> 00:22:25,600
you need to ask her.

166
00:22:27,720 --> 00:22:29,040
You know how to use it?

167
00:22:33,080 --> 00:22:34,360
I'm not that good.

168
00:22:35,000 --> 00:22:37,520
It's just that most of the photos
you saw downstairs

169
00:22:38,200 --> 00:22:39,880
were taken with this camera.

170
00:22:41,280 --> 00:22:42,480
No wonder.

171
00:22:43,120 --> 00:22:44,360
No wonder what?

172
00:22:50,400 --> 00:22:52,400
Does this model

173
00:22:53,240 --> 00:22:54,680
have problems often?

174
00:22:55,280 --> 00:22:56,720
No.

175
00:22:57,960 --> 00:23:00,760
But I suppose it depends on the user.

176
00:23:01,560 --> 00:23:03,400
If they know how to use it,

177
00:23:03,480 --> 00:23:05,400
there shouldn't be any problems.

178
00:23:09,520 --> 00:23:11,040
Well,

179
00:23:11,120 --> 00:23:13,000
Kaimook,

180
00:23:13,080 --> 00:23:15,880
can you please check
what's wrong with my friend's camera?

181
00:23:16,920 --> 00:23:19,240
The camera can't speak, Professor.

182
00:23:20,400 --> 00:23:22,400
We need to ask
the person who used it first.

183
00:23:23,000 --> 00:23:24,640
What exactly happened to it?

184
00:23:25,600 --> 00:23:27,120
Or…

185
00:23:27,200 --> 00:23:30,000
maybe someone recklessly
pushed the wrong button.

186
00:24:51,800 --> 00:24:52,880
Mr. Phum?

187
00:25:06,880 --> 00:25:08,000
Mr. Phum?

188
00:25:15,680 --> 00:25:16,840
Mr. Phum?

189
00:25:20,560 --> 00:25:21,800
Mr. Phum?

190
00:25:31,240 --> 00:25:32,400
What?

191
00:25:34,440 --> 00:25:37,400
It's not like I've never come in
while you were showering.

192
00:26:36,080 --> 00:26:37,200
What are you doing?

193
00:26:38,480 --> 00:26:39,560
Working.

194
00:26:43,160 --> 00:26:44,840
You should take a break.

195
00:26:46,120 --> 00:26:47,360
I said I'm working.

196
00:26:55,440 --> 00:26:57,320
Let's do something else first.

197
00:27:01,440 --> 00:27:03,920
I've prepared a hot tub for you.

198
00:27:06,760 --> 00:27:09,160
Hot water will help you relax.

199
00:27:13,600 --> 00:27:16,440
You must be exhausted.

200
00:27:16,520 --> 00:27:17,440
Thon.

201
00:27:25,000 --> 00:27:27,000
You're not even going to greet me?

202
00:27:34,200 --> 00:27:37,800
I'm glad you finally came home for once

203
00:27:37,880 --> 00:27:40,320
instead of staying
at your beach house all the time.

204
00:27:42,320 --> 00:27:45,200
I'm only staying here because of work.

205
00:27:46,360 --> 00:27:49,800
If it weren't necessary,
I wouldn't even set foot in this place.

206
00:27:50,680 --> 00:27:53,200
I know you're still
angry with me about your mom.

207
00:27:54,040 --> 00:27:57,480
But your mom died because of
heart disease, not because of me.

208
00:28:09,840 --> 00:28:11,680
I'm a man

209
00:28:12,720 --> 00:28:14,120
without heart disease,

210
00:28:15,120 --> 00:28:17,400
and seeing that scene just now
almost gave me a heart attack.

211
00:28:18,840 --> 00:28:20,360
Imagine how Mom felt.

212
00:28:24,000 --> 00:28:24,960
I…

213
00:28:25,040 --> 00:28:27,120
Don't bring it up again.

214
00:28:28,040 --> 00:28:29,280
I don't want to hear it.

215
00:28:35,520 --> 00:28:38,640
Why did you buy that girl's photographs?

216
00:28:39,640 --> 00:28:40,880
What are you talking about?

217
00:28:42,640 --> 00:28:45,280
Oh, Kaimook?

218
00:28:46,040 --> 00:28:47,080
What wrong with that?

219
00:28:48,280 --> 00:28:49,440
Because someone like you

220
00:28:50,280 --> 00:28:52,440
never does anything
without expecting something in return.

221
00:28:54,720 --> 00:28:58,160
What photographs?
And who is this Kaimook girl?

222
00:29:02,040 --> 00:29:03,920
Someone like me can do good things too.

223
00:29:05,120 --> 00:29:08,000
I bought them
because I wanted to make merit.

224
00:29:08,080 --> 00:29:11,480
Kaimook is going to use the money

225
00:29:11,560 --> 00:29:12,920
for a marine conservation project.

226
00:29:16,680 --> 00:29:18,200
May the merit

227
00:29:19,280 --> 00:29:23,240
help free you
from your endless lust someday.

228
00:29:34,280 --> 00:29:37,120
So who exactly is Kaimook?

229
00:29:37,200 --> 00:29:39,080
And how do you know her?

230
00:29:42,960 --> 00:29:43,840
Hey…

231
00:31:00,040 --> 00:31:02,120
Mom! Mom!

232
00:31:03,640 --> 00:31:04,800
Mom.

233
00:31:07,480 --> 00:31:09,400
Mom, what's wrong?

234
00:31:09,480 --> 00:31:10,560
Nuan.

235
00:31:10,640 --> 00:31:12,280
Mom! Mom!

236
00:31:15,760 --> 00:31:17,320
Mom! Mom!

237
00:31:18,720 --> 00:31:19,560
Mom!

238
00:31:20,640 --> 00:31:21,640
Mom.

239
00:31:44,880 --> 00:31:46,160
Hello?

240
00:31:46,840 --> 00:31:50,320
It's Kaimook. I'm calling
to update you about the camera.

241
00:31:50,400 --> 00:31:51,560
<i>So what's wrong with it?</i>

242
00:31:52,280 --> 00:31:53,760
I don't know.

243
00:31:53,840 --> 00:31:56,560
From what I checked,
nothing seems wrong with it.

244
00:31:56,640 --> 00:31:59,360
If nothing's wrong, then why…?

245
00:32:00,120 --> 00:32:02,760
I don't know. I've never encountered

246
00:32:02,840 --> 00:32:04,480
a case like this before.

247
00:32:04,560 --> 00:32:07,760
I didn't know what else to do,
so I sent it to the shop.

248
00:32:07,840 --> 00:32:10,200
You can contact them tomorrow.

249
00:32:11,040 --> 00:32:12,160
Which shop?

250
00:32:13,200 --> 00:32:15,120
Which shop did you buy the camera from?

251
00:32:16,320 --> 00:32:18,520
Okay, got it.

252
00:32:19,720 --> 00:32:20,960
Anything else?

253
00:32:22,480 --> 00:32:24,160
- Yes.
<i>- What?</i>

254
00:32:25,400 --> 00:32:26,840
A thank you.

255
00:32:26,920 --> 00:32:28,520
Do you know how to say it?

256
00:32:28,600 --> 00:32:31,280
I do. Thanks.

257
00:32:32,640 --> 00:32:35,240
Very good. Goodbye.

258
00:32:39,160 --> 00:32:40,400
What a jerk.

259
00:33:21,480 --> 00:33:24,200
Going diving?! The boat's about to leave.

260
00:33:24,800 --> 00:33:25,680
DIVING

261
00:33:25,760 --> 00:33:28,080
Hop on the boat.

262
00:33:28,160 --> 00:33:29,320
The boat's about to leave

263
00:33:33,280 --> 00:33:35,480
You wanna go diving?
The boat's about to leave.

264
00:33:35,560 --> 00:33:36,600
What do you think?

265
00:33:38,760 --> 00:33:41,480
- Let's go.
- You're going? This way.

266
00:33:43,120 --> 00:33:45,880
Wait for me. Na.

267
00:33:45,960 --> 00:33:47,560
- I'm coming, honey.
- Ugh.

268
00:33:50,640 --> 00:33:52,000
Sorry for…

269
00:33:55,400 --> 00:33:57,400
For making everyone wait.

270
00:34:03,240 --> 00:34:04,640
- Everyone's here now, right?
- Yes.

271
00:34:04,720 --> 00:34:05,800
I'll set sail then.

272
00:34:21,880 --> 00:34:22,840
Looks good.

273
00:34:29,800 --> 00:34:32,400
Alright. Turn left a little bit.

274
00:34:33,120 --> 00:34:36,400
Nice. Just a bit.

275
00:34:36,480 --> 00:34:39,719
One, two, three.

276
00:34:39,800 --> 00:34:41,679
One, two, three. Good.

277
00:34:43,600 --> 00:34:45,880
Let me see.

278
00:34:45,960 --> 00:34:48,000
- Here. Isn't it nice?
- Let me see.

279
00:34:49,040 --> 00:34:52,600
- Na, I can't see the sea.
- It's here. This looks good.

280
00:34:52,679 --> 00:34:55,280
Hm. You could take
the same shot at the Mekong River.

281
00:34:55,360 --> 00:34:57,360
- Take it again. Get the wide open sea.
- Alright.

282
00:34:57,440 --> 00:34:58,440
Okay.

283
00:34:58,520 --> 00:35:00,360
- Okay.
- Make sure you capture the sea.

284
00:35:00,440 --> 00:35:01,480
Okay.

285
00:35:05,800 --> 00:35:07,160
Hello, Professor.

286
00:35:08,120 --> 00:35:09,520
Kaimook?

287
00:35:09,600 --> 00:35:11,840
I didn't expect to see you here.

288
00:35:11,920 --> 00:35:13,320
It's school break.

289
00:35:13,400 --> 00:35:16,360
I gotta find something exciting to do.

290
00:35:21,560 --> 00:35:24,800
So, about your friend's camera…

291
00:35:25,520 --> 00:35:28,840
Well, he already got a replacement.

292
00:35:28,920 --> 00:35:31,520
Hopefully, this one won't fail him again.

293
00:35:33,640 --> 00:35:35,600
I'm honestly asking, Professor.

294
00:35:36,240 --> 00:35:38,040
Does your friend

295
00:35:38,120 --> 00:35:40,200
even know how to use a camera?

296
00:35:40,840 --> 00:35:43,720
Of course, he does. Why?

297
00:35:46,080 --> 00:35:49,880
I don't think the camera was broken.

298
00:35:49,960 --> 00:35:52,960
I think your friend
just doesn't know how to shoot properly.

299
00:35:55,040 --> 00:35:57,120
Really?

300
00:35:58,040 --> 00:36:01,200
Well, please tell your friend

301
00:36:01,280 --> 00:36:04,640
that if he's still not
very good at photography,

302
00:36:04,720 --> 00:36:06,520
he should just use auto mode.

303
00:36:07,280 --> 00:36:08,840
At least the pictures
won't come out ruined.

304
00:36:08,920 --> 00:36:11,440
Alright. I'll tell him.

305
00:36:12,280 --> 00:36:15,520
Alright then, I'll go change.

306
00:36:15,600 --> 00:36:17,640
- Have fun diving.
- Okay.

307
00:36:41,440 --> 00:36:44,640
Hey, someone once told me

308
00:36:45,280 --> 00:36:47,280
this area is cursed.

309
00:36:52,560 --> 00:36:54,160
A real story or just a legend?

310
00:36:56,040 --> 00:36:57,440
What kind of curse?

311
00:36:59,440 --> 00:37:01,640
They say

312
00:37:01,720 --> 00:37:04,000
people who come here

313
00:37:04,800 --> 00:37:06,080
rarely make it back.

314
00:37:08,800 --> 00:37:10,360
People just like to spread rumors.

315
00:37:17,160 --> 00:37:20,000
If you're scared,
you don't have to go down.

316
00:37:21,200 --> 00:37:22,640
If something happens to you,

317
00:37:22,720 --> 00:37:24,400
everyone else will be in trouble.

318
00:37:26,800 --> 00:37:28,440
I'm not scared.

319
00:37:29,080 --> 00:37:30,640
Just surprised.

320
00:37:31,360 --> 00:37:32,960
I've

321
00:37:33,040 --> 00:37:35,280
never heard that story before either.

322
00:37:36,840 --> 00:37:38,440
Most importantly,

323
00:37:39,160 --> 00:37:41,240
I've dived around here many times.

324
00:37:42,280 --> 00:37:44,520
I'm not going to cause trouble for anyone.

325
00:37:52,440 --> 00:37:53,680
We're here.

326
00:37:53,760 --> 00:37:56,640
You can jump in from this point.
The boat will be around this area.

327
00:37:56,720 --> 00:37:57,640
Okay.

328
00:38:00,080 --> 00:38:01,880
Are we there yet?

329
00:38:01,960 --> 00:38:04,920
I can't wait to see the coral reefs.

330
00:38:05,920 --> 00:38:06,920
Are we there yet?

331
00:38:07,800 --> 00:38:10,240
Mana, why are you so slow?

332
00:38:10,320 --> 00:38:13,040
Don't stray away from your buddy.

333
00:38:13,120 --> 00:38:14,680
There are whirlpools around here.

334
00:38:14,760 --> 00:38:16,280
If you run into one,
back away immediately.

335
00:38:17,960 --> 00:38:19,160
Yes.

336
00:42:49,800 --> 00:42:51,360
Who took my child?!

337
00:43:01,120 --> 00:43:02,520
Help me!

338
00:43:05,640 --> 00:43:07,120
But this house is haunted.

339
00:43:07,200 --> 00:43:09,160
Then why doesn't it haunt anyone else?

340
00:43:09,240 --> 00:43:11,200
Why is it only haunting you?

341
00:43:12,600 --> 00:43:14,160
Mr. Narathon…

342
00:43:14,240 --> 00:43:16,960
<i>When the time comes,</i>
<i>no matter how hard you try to stop it,</i>

343
00:43:17,040 --> 00:43:19,400
they're destined to meet anyway.

344
00:43:49,000 --> 00:43:50,800
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
